            "answer_text": "The word \u201cRagnarok\u201d comes from the Old Norse Ragnar\u00f6k - \u201cfate of the Gods.\u201d Not many gods will survive Ragnarok. The known survivors are: Aegir, Vidar, Vali, Hoenir, Vili, Magni, Modi, Herm\u00f3\u00f0r, Forseti and Ullr. Most of the goddesses, however, will survive: Frigg, Freya, Sif, Thrud, Idun, Saga, Eir, Gefjun, Fulla, Sjofn, Lofn, Var, Vor, Syn and Hlin. The goddesses Snotra and Gna will die. Ragnarok - Norse Mythology for Smart People ",
